<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-06T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20252/12–644: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06T18:00:00+01:00">December 6, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received December 7—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3961. Despatch 3389, November 9.<note n="83" xml:id="d601fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> A note has now been received from the Spanish
                                Foreign Office dated November 27 in reply to Embassy’s <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> 827, November 6 supplying lists
                                of names of the following: <list>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>53 German agents expelled from North Africa plus 5 who are
                                        to leave shortly. This list includes name of an unknown
                                        individual not appearing in Tangier’s despatch 2470,
                                        November 25;<note n="83" xml:id="d601fn2">Not
                                            printed.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <pb facs="0565" n="553" xml:id="pg_553"/>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>36 German agents ordered interned at Caldas and 3 ordered
                                        interned at other unspecified places about which we propose
                                        to get specific data;</item>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>750 German customs guards and officials transferred to
                                        Sobrón from Miranda concentration camp, the remaining 500
                                        others at Miranda, names of whom are promised. Reourtel
                                        3807, November 21, 3 p.m. Despatch follows.<note n="84" xml:id="d601fn3">Despatch 3583, not printed.</note>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <p>Following oral representations to the Under Secretary the Foreign
                                Office includes written undertaking that orders have been given
                                prohibiting interned foreigners from using the interurban
                                telephone.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Tangier by courier.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>